<br>
Sure EQ wasn't perfect. But it still has one thing better than all other new games, a means to meet other people easily.<br>
<br>
All new games go for wide open areas. Frankly, this is killing the genre. Its fucking hard to meet people on the other side of the planet. Someone walks into the zone and shouts lfg, thats a person thats right there and lfg. EQ now has the framework to allow a person lfg anywhere to get to your group with relative simplicity.<br>
<br>
SWG's problem was grouping was almost useless for most classes, you could max your entire class in like 2 weeks.<br>
<br>
EQ is the last Sony game I'm going to pay for. Amazingly, SWG's CS was worse than EQs. Shouldn't come as any suprise though. I made a ticket, 4 days later got a response to leave times I'd be online and a service rep would contact me. 2 weeks later nothing. Account ran out, I didn't mourn it. This teaches me sony doesn't give a fuck about us. I knew that before but I would have thought in a new game they'd at least ramp up CS staff to deal with extra complaints from a new game.<br>
<br>
Sure the game wasn't golden in the Brad McQuaid years, but it isn't now. At least then it seemed that they cared about their customers. Only reason I've stayed is there is no better mmorpg out at the moment and my friends are here. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=477296">Kerai</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
