Fuck you Jhello for breaking my Mezzes~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bakxs>Bakxs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1070<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/26/03 6:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2167.topic&index=41>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Closed Minded</span><hr size=1> It's easy to pick on certain titles/games for being very limited and one-dimensional.  Not to mention, games that appeal to one person may or may not appeal to another.  A lot of it comes to personal preference.  I know a lot of people that don't like CS and I know some people that love Diablo.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, when you think about a company--especially a large company such as Sony--even more so that it's a publicly traded company, the main job of the executives/managers of the company is to make as much profit for the stakeholders of the company.  If it means that Ayiar has to wait 5 days to get an answer on his petition to make $XX.XX more profit, so be it.  They have to judge whether or not Ayiar will quit over the lower CS quality and whether his decision to quit or not (and stop the revenue stream) is worth it over the increased cost of additional/higher quality customer service.  <br>
<br>
In this case, I guess the bean-counters were right.  All those that are playing EQ either have experienced the poor service or know someone very well who has or even heard horror stories of such.  Guess what, they are still playing.  I'm not saying Sony is doing the right thing.  Actually, as you and others have demonstrated--people may not purchase their next game.  But when push comes to shove, I would guess that those are only empty words.  Case in point: PlanetSide &amp; SWG.  You know Sony is notorious for poor service.  Yet you still purchased those two games.  Now you say that is it and no more for Sony.  EQ2 or whatever future game/expansion will come out...  I'm guessing that many who play EQ now, no matter how bad their experience with the CS team has been and how disgusted with how Sony has treated them will still probably try the game.  How many of you are going to buy LDoN in the hopes it lives up to Sony's promises?  How many people will buy it hoping it's completed on release.  Fool me once, shame on you.  Fool me twice, shame on me...<br>
<br>
Of course, many will stand by their principles.  But when real life friends start playing it or long-time gaming friends gush on how great the next great game is...  the bad CS of the past is conveniently forgotten.  When problems arise...  let the bitch fest begin.  Once again, I can see the clamoring that Sony is &quot;teh debil&quot; and that you will never buy another product of theirs again...  until the next game or expansion comes out of course.  <br>
<br>
When it comes to games and movies...  while there will be winners and losers, I really think it boils down to individual titles.  Past success and failures does influence...  but if a game is really good or bad, it will succeed and fail on its own merits--especially in the current trend of the subscriber profit model.  <br>
<br>
I find it funny that you slam Diablo for being a product easily to finish and get bored of--and yet you are looking forward to WoW.  Who is to say that Blizzard might do the same to WoW?  <br>
<br>
EverQuest was a very large success.  Even with all its flaws and all these other games that have attempted to unseat it--it still enjoys much success and popularity.  While I will gladly admit, I am looking forward to WoW.  It is looking to be an awesome game--I still know it could end up being a piece of shit.  Just as I, like many others don't think EQ2 will be any good--but who knows?  Sony and EQ has fought off all these challengers with pretty good success...  who am I to doubt them?<br>
<br>
--Bakxs <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=2167.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=2167.topic&start=41&stop=41>3</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=2167.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showNextMessage?topicID=2167.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2167.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.threadControl?topicID=2167.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2167.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2167.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub41.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><